{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1457,"text":"Our world has many superheroes."},{"time":4454,"text":"But they have the worst of\nall superpowers: invisibility."},{"time":10012,"text":"For example, the catadores,"},{"time":12349,"text":"workers who collect recyclable \nmaterials for a living."},{"time":16462,"text":"Catadores emerged from \nsocial inequality, unemployment,"},{"time":21122,"text":"and the abundance of solid waste"},{"time":24141,"text":"from the deficiency of the \nwaste collection system."},{"time":28740,"text":"Catadores provide a heavy, \nhonest and essential work"},{"time":34500,"text":"that benefits the entire population.\nBut they are not acknowledged for it."},{"time":39441,"text":"Here in Brazil, they collect 90 percent\nof all the waste that's actually recycled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47442,"text":"Most of the catadores work independently,"},{"time":50164,"text":"picking waste from the streets and \nselling to junk yards at very low prices."},{"time":55575,"text":"They may collect over 300 kilos"},{"time":58970,"text":"in their bags, shopping carts, \nbicycles and carroças."},{"time":64505,"text":"Carroças are carts\nbuilt from wood or metal"},{"time":67351,"text":"and found in several streets in Brazil,"},{"time":70169,"text":"much like graffiti and street art."},{"time":72792,"text":"And this is how I first met these \nmarginalized superheroes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77743,"text":"I am a graffiti artist and activist"},{"time":80023,"text":"and my art is social, environmental \nand political in nature."},{"time":86208,"text":"In 2007, I took my work beyond walls\nand onto the carroças,"},{"time":91370,"text":"as a new urban support for my message."},{"time":94324,"text":"But at this time, \ngiving voice to the catadores."},{"time":98141,"text":"By adding art and humor to the cause,\nit became more appealing,"},{"time":103482,"text":"which helped call attention \nto the catadores"},{"time":106050,"text":"and improve their self-esteem."},{"time":107975,"text":"And also, they are famous now \non the streets, on mass media and social."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113256,"text":"So, the thing is,"},{"time":115945,"text":"I plunged into this universe \nand have not stopped working since."},{"time":119902,"text":"I have painted over 200 \ncarroças in many cities"},{"time":123336,"text":"and have been invited to do exhibitions \nand trips worldwide."},{"time":127301,"text":"And then I realized that catadores,\nin their invisibility,"},{"time":131953,"text":"are not exclusive to Brazil."},{"time":133981,"text":"I met them in Argentina, Chile,"},{"time":138505,"text":"Bolivia, South Africa, Turkey"},{"time":143079,"text":"and even in developed countries such\nas the United States and Japan."},{"time":148104,"text":"And this was when I realized that I needed\nto have more people join the cause"},{"time":152820,"text":"because it's a big challenge."},{"time":154653,"text":"And then, I created a collaborative \nmovement called Pimp My Carroça --"},{"time":160455,"text":"(Laughter) -- which is \na large crowdfunded event."},{"time":164142,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":165169,"text":"(Applause)."},{"time":168868,"text":"So Pimp My Carroça is a large \ncrowdfunded event"},{"time":172840,"text":"to help catadores and their carroças."},{"time":175576,"text":"Catadores are assisted by well-being \nprofessionals and healthcare,"},{"time":179635,"text":"like physicians, dentists, podiatrists, \nhair stylists, massage therapists"},{"time":186393,"text":"and much more."},{"time":187698,"text":"But also, they also receive safety shirts,\ngloves, raincoats and eyeglasses"},{"time":192667,"text":"to see in high-definition the city,"},{"time":194762,"text":"while their carroças are renovated\nby our incredible volunteers."},{"time":199780,"text":"And then they receive safety items, too:"},{"time":202189,"text":"reflective tapes, horns and mirrors."},{"time":204554,"text":"Then, finally, painted by a street artist"},{"time":207119,"text":"and become part of part of this huge, \namazing mobile art exhibition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212420,"text":"Pimp My Carroça took to the streets\nof São Paulo, Rio de Janeiro and Curitiba."},{"time":218208,"text":"But to meet the demand in other cities,\nincluding outside of Brazil,"},{"time":222907,"text":"we have created Pimpx,\nwhich is inspired by TEDx,"},{"time":228092,"text":"and it's a simplified, do-it-yourself,\ncrowdfunded edition of Pimp My Carroça."},{"time":234026,"text":"So now everybody can join."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237016,"text":"In two years, over 170 catadores,\n800 volunteers and 200 street artists"},{"time":245150,"text":"and more than 1,000 donors"},{"time":247126,"text":"have been involved in the \nPimp My Carroça movement,"},{"time":250001,"text":"whose actions have even been used\nin teaching recycling at a local school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256095,"text":"So catadores are leaving \ninvisibility behind"},{"time":260108,"text":"and becoming increasingly\nrespected and valued."},{"time":263662,"text":"Because of their pimped carroças,\nthey are able to fight back to prejudice,"},{"time":268219,"text":"increase their income and \ntheir interaction with society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272121,"text":"So now, I'd like to challenge you \nto start looking at and acknowledging"},{"time":277043,"text":"the catadores and other \ninvisible superheroes from your city."},{"time":281065,"text":"Try to see the world as one, \nwithout boundaries or frontiers."},{"time":286134,"text":"Believe it or not,"},{"time":287764,"text":"there are over 20 million \ncatadores worldwide."},{"time":293785,"text":"So next time you see one,"},{"time":296405,"text":"recognize them as a vital part\nof our society."},{"time":301066,"text":"Muito obrigado, thank you."},{"time":303710,"text":"(Applause)."}]}]}